AboutMe:
I'm a(n) (ex)-Flex developer in Chicago, I also play around with Arduino, Processing, Java, have a small history with C/C++. I worked for a company called Roundarch Isobar where I work primarily on web-applications built in Flex and service layer code using Java (Spring, iBatis, BlazeDS) and Teradata from 2009-2012. Since then I've been learning the ropes in AngularJS, porting some knowledge and building web-apps. Mid 2013 I'm starting my own consulting business and am currently working on an urban agriculture project for mapping sites in Chicago and tracking crop growth information.

I love programming (or rather problem solving) and helping people out is okay too. I ultimately went to DePaul University and received a BS in Computer Science.
